T1  - Conceptual and Normative Aspects of International Management
AU  - Kolde, Endel J.
AU  - Hill, Richard E.
Y1  - 1967/06/01
PY  - 1967
DA  - 1967/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254631
DO  - 10.5465/254631
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 119
EP  - 128
VL  - 10
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A multinational enterprise operates in a plurality of dynamic environments. Its organizational structure, therefore, must consist of two parts: (1) a nationally and culturally decentralized base designed to deal with pluralistic conditions through strong, autonomous subentities and (2) a centralized superstructure to achieve coordination throughout the whole. Coordination is predicated on effective international communication ? both its linguistic and non-linguistic aspects. Good communication, in turn, requires comparability of standards, rapid feedback and multiple management.
AB  - A multinational enterprise operates in a plurality of dynamic environments. Its organizational structure, therefore, must consist of two parts: (1) a nationally and culturally decentralized base designed to deal with pluralistic conditions through strong, autonomous subentities and (2) a centralized superstructure to achieve coordination throughout the whole. Coordination is predicated on effective international communication ? both its linguistic and non-linguistic aspects. Good communication, in turn, requires comparability of standards, rapid feedback and multiple management.
